WHICH philosophy schools are widly accpeted by others and WHY?

INTRODUCTION

No matter what fields we are in, as long as there are different schools, there are competitions and cooperation, like policy, artistry, and wizarding. Also, when coming to a particular science field, some theories of a certain school are more widely accepted by others while some remain controversial. For example, relativity theory is hardly rejected, while whether there are parallel universes remains a myth.

So intuitively, I'm wondering are there schools that are more acceptable to all the other schools?¶

If there are, why?¶

Methodology

✨Which are popular¶

Q: Attitude of a school towards others?¶

A: Calculate the proportion of positive attitude of each school article towards other schools' names and authors.

Q: Frequency of a school mentioned by others?¶

A: Calculate the frequency of each school's article mentioning other school name and their authors.

✨Why are they¶

Q: Talking about?¶

A: Classify topics mentioned by certain schools.

🕶 Continental school is strongly against by Analytic school.¶

"So analytic philosophy is concerned with analysis analysis of thought, language, logic, knowledge, mind, etc; whereas continental philosophy is concerned with synthesis synthesis of modernity with history, individuals with society, and speculation with application."\ -- Kile Jones

https://philosophynow.org/issues/74/Analytic_versus_Continental_Philosophy#:~:text=So%20analytic%20philosophy%20is%20concerned,society%2C%20and%20speculation%20with%20application

🕶 Rationalism school is against by Empiricism school.¶

"The disagreement between rationalism and empiricism primarily concerns the second question, regarding the sources of our concepts and knowledge. In some instances, the disagreement on this topic results in conflicting responses to the other questions as well. The disagreement may extend to incorporate the nature of warrant or where the limits of our thought and knowledge are."\ -- Peter Markie

https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/rationalism-empiricism/

🕶 Feminism school is going against the phenomenology school.¶

"Phenomenology and feminism are rarely associated, either in or out of the context of film studies. The reasons for this disjunction are strikingly obvious at first glance. The former stands as a paragon of male philosophical observation. The latter proclaims its interest in transforming an oppressive system rather than being content with interpreting it If philosophical reflection must achieve a polite distanciation from its object of study, the notion of a feminist revolutionary philosophy certainly must be perceived as an oxymoron." -- Gaylyn Studlar

https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/10509209009361353?journalCode=gqrf20

🕶 Capitalism school is controversial.¶

"Critics argue that capitalism is associated with the unfair distribution of wealth and power; a tendency toward market monopoly or oligopoly (and government by oligarchy); imperialism, counter-revolutionary wars and various forms of economic and cultural exploitation; repression of workers and trade unionists and phenomena such as social alienation, economic inequality, unemployment and economic instability. " -- wiki

In [13]:
pro_approve = attitude_matrix.to_numpy()
pro_mentioned = freq_matrix.to_numpy()
X,Y = [],[]
for i in range(len(pro_approve)):
    x = round(np.sum(np.array(pro_approve[i]) >= 0, axis=0)/len(pro_approve[i]),2)
    y = sum(pro_mentioned[i]) - pro_mentioned[i][i]
    X.append(x)
    Y.append(y)
Att = pd.DataFrame(index = attitude_matrix.index)
Att['Posstive rate'] = X
Att['Citation times'] = Y
Att.sort_values(['Citation times','Posstive rate'],ascending = False)

What does these two school talking about?

Here are two versions of each of them. One is from the philosophy scholars and the other one is from algorithm analysis.

👑 German idealism¶

SCHOLARS conclusion:¶

"Knowledge is constituted by the sensible contents derived from the object of cognition and the a priori forms in the faculties of the mind. Thus, things considered in themselves, apart from the way mind organizes sensible contents, are in principle unknowable. With this argument, God and the soul became inaccessible because they do not exhibit sensible content. While Kant rejected the epistemological possibility of knowing God, he affirmed the possibility of knowledge in the realm of morality. Nevertheless, Kant relegated various theological concepts such as God and the immortality of soul from the realm of knowledge."

ALGORITHM conclusion:¶

  • Topic I: Existence of world is abstract.
  • Topic II: Ethical law of human and self consciousness.
  • Topic III: Relationship between self consciousness, nature essence, and universal recognition.

👑 Rationalism¶

SCHOLARS conclusion:¶

"Rationalism, in Western philosophy, is the view that regards reason as the chief source and test of knowledge. Holding that reality itself has an inherently logical structure, the rationalist asserts that a class of truths exists that the intellect can grasp directly. There are, according to the rationalists, certain rational principlesespecially in logic and mathematics, and even in ethics and metaphysicsthat are so fundamental that to deny them is to fall into contradiction. Rationalism is the epistemological view that "regards reason as the chief source and test of knowledge" or "any view appealing to reason as a source of knowledge or justification". More formally, rationalism is defined as a methodology or a theory "in which the criterion of the truth is not sensory but intellectual and deductive"."

ALGORITHM conclusion:¶

  • Topic 1: Human spirit and body motions.
  • Topic 2: God, nature and knowledge.
  • Topic 3: Vortexes between god and minds.
